ions exist'' in the security policies, creating a direct bypass vulnerability. While MFA is enabled for admin access (Q12), it doesn''t prevent exploitation of existing exclusions. The effectiveness of 24/7 SOC monitoring (Q14) is reduced if activity within excluded paths is not properly logged or reviewed, as per the identified vulnerability. Given the critical nature of ''Manufacturing Line Control'' (Q5) and the clear bypass, the probability of exploitation is ''High'' (once every 1-3 months)."\n      },\n      "risk_value": {\n        "value": 16,\n        "calculation": "4 (impact) \u00d7 4 (probability) = 16"\n      },\n      "risk_evaluation_rating": {\n        "rating": 4,\n        "level": "Risk Rating 4",\n        "mapping_rationale": "Risk value 16 falls into the 16-20 range, which maps to ''Risk Rating 4'' per the discovered risk level mapping (Table 6)."\n      },\n      "risk_classification": {\n        "classification": "NON-ACCEPTABLE",\n        "criteria_applied": "Risk Ratings 3-5 are Non Acceptable Risk",\n        "justification": "Risk Rating 4 is classified as ''NON-ACCEPTABLE'' per organizational policy (Table 7)."\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  "rag_queries_performed": [\n    "risk quantification methodology",\n    "risk calculation formula"\n  ],\n  "rag_sources_consulted": [\n    "Risk Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx",\n    "ISO IEC 27005-2022.pdf"\n  ]\n}','\n',char(10)),replace('{\n  "discovery_summary": {\n    "control_framework": "ISO 27001:2022 (primary for controls), IT General Controls (ITGC)",\n    "control_categories": [\n      "Organizational Controls (ISO)",\n      "People Controls (ISO)",\n      "Physical Controls (ISO)",\n      "Technological Controls (ISO)",\n      "Access to Programs and Data (ITGC)",\n      "Program Change Management (ITGC)",\n      "Program Development (ITGC)",\n      "Computer Operations (ITGC)",\n      "System / Infrastructure Security (ITGC)",\n      "IT Governance / Policy Management