ession system relies solely on ''Fire Extinguishers,'' indicating a severe lack of automatic fire detection and suppression systems (e.g., sprinklers, gas suppression for data centers). A fire originating in the data center or other critical areas could rapidly spread, causing extensive damage to IT infrastructure, corporate administrative functions, and executive offices, leading to a complete cessation of IT service delivery, customer support, and product development, impacting 1000 personnel and critical business processes.", "risk_statement": "Risk of data center outage and extensive building damage from fire due to inadequate automatic fire detection and suppression systems, potentially causing prolonged business interruption, loss of critical IT services, and significant financial losses.", "vulnerabilities": [{"vulnerability": "Absence of adequate fire detection and firefighting equipment (e.g., sprinklers, automatic suppression systems).", "description": "Absence of adequate fire detection and firefighting equipment (e.g., sprinklers, automatic suppression systems)."}, {"vulnerability": "Lack of inspection / malfunctioning of fire-fighting, fire-suppression, fire alerting and fire exits (implied by only manual extinguishers).", "description": "Lack of inspection / malfunctioning of fire-fighting, fire-suppression, fire alerting and fire exits (implied by only manual extinguishers)."}, {"vulnerability": "Lack of monitoring procedures for temperature and humidity controls (for data center, increasing fire risk).", "description": "Lack of monitoring procedures for temperature and humidity controls (for data center, increasing fire risk)."}], "evidence": ["3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts] Q: What type of fire detection and suppression systems are installed in the building? \u2192 Answer: [''Fire Extinguishers'']", "2. Business Context and Criticality] Q: If ''Yes'' to the above, please list the critical business functions or departments housed withi