 helps understand the scope of potential impacts."}, "Q_BUSINESS_CRITICALITY": {"question_text": "What is the overall Asset Criticality Classification of this Office Building to the organization''s operations?", "answer": "Medium Critical - Medium impact on business if C,I and A of asset gets compromised", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "2. Business Context and Criticality", "help_text": "Consider the overall impact on business if the building''s confidentiality, integrity, and availability were compromised.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Provides a high-level understanding of the asset''s importance, guiding the prioritization of risk assessment efforts.", "why_this_matters": "Provides a high-level understanding of the asset''s importance, guiding the prioritization of risk assessment efforts."}, "Q_OCCUPANCY_COUNT": {"question_text": "Approximately how many personnel (employees, contractors, visitors) occupy or regularly use this Office Building?", "answer": 1000, "question_type": "number", "section": "2. Business Context and Criticality", "help_text": "Provide an average or maximum number of people present during operational hours.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Indicates the potential impact on human safety and business continuity in case of an incident.", "why_this_matters": "Indicates the potential impact on human safety and business continuity in case of an incident."}, "Q_CRITICAL_FUNCTIONS_HOUSED": {"question_text": "Does this Office Building house any critical business functions or departments (e.g., data center, executive offices, primary call center)?", "answer": "Yes", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "2. Business Context and Criticality", "help_text": "Select ''Yes'' if essential operations that cannot be easily relocated are performed here.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Highlights specific areas of high business impact if the building is compromised or unavailable.", "why_this_matters": "Highlights specific areas of high business impact if the building is compromised or unavailable."}, "Q_CRITICAL_FUNCTIONS_LIST": {"question_text": "If ''Yes'' to the above, please list the critical business functions or departments housed within this building.", "answer": "data center, executive offices, primary call center", "question_type": "textarea", "section": "2. Business Context and Criticality", "help_text": "e.g., ''Primary IT Data Center, Finance Department, Executive Leadership, Customer Support Call Center''\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Provides specific details on critical dependencies, aiding in impact analysis.", "why_this_matters": "Provides specific details on critical dependencies, aiding in impact analysis."}, "Q_DEPENDENT_BUSINESS_PROCESSES": {"question_text": "Which key business processes are directly dependent on the continuous operation of this Office Building?", "answer": "Daily administrative operations, IT service delivery, customer support, product development", "question_type": "textarea", "section": "2. Business Context and Criticality", "help_text": "e.g., ''Daily administrative operations, IT service delivery, customer support, product development''\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Helps identify the scope of business disruption if the building becomes unavailable.", "why_this_matters": "Helps identify the scope of business disruption if the building becomes unavailable."}, "Q_PHYSICAL_ACCESS_CONTROLS": {"question_text": "What primary physical access control systems are in place for the building perimeter and critical internal areas?", "answer": ["Security Guards (Business Hours)"], "question_type": "multiselect", "section": "3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts", "help_text": "Select all applicable access control mechanisms.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Provides facts about controls preventing unauthorized physical access, impacting confidentiality and integrity of assets within.", "why_this_matters": "Provides facts about controls preventing unauthorized physical access, impacting confidentiality and integrity of assets within."}, "Q_SURVEILLANCE_CAMERAS": {"question_text": "Are surveillance cameras (CCTV) installed and actively monitored within and around the Office Building?", "answer": "Yes, but not actively monitored", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts", "help_text": "Indicate the level of monitoring for surveillance systems.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Fact about detective controls for physical security incidents, aiding in incident response and forensics.", "why_this_matters": "Fact about detective controls for physical security incidents, aiding in incident response and forensics."}, "Q_ALARM_SYSTEMS": {"question_text": "Are alarm systems (e.g., intrusion detection, motion sensors) installed and monitored?", "answer": "Yes, local alarms only", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts", "help_text": "Specify if alarms are connected to a central monitoring station or are local only.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Fact about detective controls for unauthorized entry, contributing to the overall security posture.", "why_this_matters": "Fact about detective controls for unauthorized entry, contributing to the overall security posture."}, "Q_FIRE_SUPPRESSION_SYSTEM": {"question_text": "What type of fire detection and suppression systems are installed in the building?", "answer": ["Fire Extinguishers"], "question_type": "multiselect", "section": "3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts", "help_text": "Select all applicable fire safety systems.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Facts about controls mitigating fire risks, directly impacting availability and safety.", "why_this_matters": "Facts about controls mitigating fire risks, directly impacting availability and safety."}, "Q_UTILITY_REDUNDANCY": {"question_text": "Are there redundant power sources (e.g., UPS, generators) or internet connectivity options for critical operations within the building?", "answer": "Yes, for internet only", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts", "help_text": "Indicate if backup systems are in place for essential utilities.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Facts about controls ensuring availability of critical services, reducing downtime risk.", "why_this_matters": "Facts about controls ensuring availability of critical services, reducing downtime risk."}, "Q_ENVIRONMENTAL_RISKS": {"question_text": "Is the Office Building located in an area prone to specific environmental risks (e.g., flood zone, seismic activity, severe weather)?", "answer": "Yes", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts", "help_text": "Consider local geographical and meteorological conditions.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Identifies external threat factors that could impact the building''s availability and integrity.", "why_this_matters": "Identifies external threat factors that could impact the building''s availability and integrity."}, "Q_ENVIRONMENTAL_RISKS_DETAILS": {"question_text": "If ''Yes'' to the above, please specify the environmental risks.", "answer": " flood zone, seismic activity, severe weather", "question_type": "textarea", "section": "3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts", "help_text": "e.g., ''Located in a 100-year flood plain, high seismic activity zone, frequent hurricanes''\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Provides specific details for assessing the likelihood and potential impact of natural disasters.", "why_this_matters": "Provides specific details for assessing the likelihood and potential impact of natural disasters."}, "Q_EMERGENCY_EVACUATION_PLAN": {"question_text": "Is there a documented and regularly practiced emergency evacuation plan for the Office Building?", "answer": "Yes, documented but not regularly practiced", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "4. Emergency Preparedness and Operational Controls", "help_text": "Indicate if the plan is not only documented but also tested.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Fact about a control for personnel safety and orderly response during emergencies, impacting human safety and business continuity.", "why_this_matters": "Fact about a control for personnel safety and orderly response during emergencies, impacting human safety and business continuity."}, "Q_DISASTER_RECOVERY_PLAN": {"question_text": "Is there a disaster recovery or business continuity plan specifically addressing the unavailability of this Office Building?", "answer": "Yes, documented but not tested", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "4. Emergency Preparedness and Operational Controls", "help_text": "Indicate if a plan exists to continue operations if the building is unusable.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Fact about a control for business continuity, directly impacting the availability of services and operations.", "why_this_matters": "Fact about a control for business continuity, directly impacting the availability of services and operations."}, "Q_INCIDENT_RESPONSE_PLAN": {"question_text": "Is there an incident response plan for physical security incidents (e.g., unauthorized entry, theft, vandalism) specific to this building?", "answer": "Yes, documented but not practiced", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "4. Emergency Preparedness and Operational Controls", "help_text": "Indicate if a plan exists to respond to physical security breaches.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Fact about a control for managing and mitigating the impact of physical security incidents.", "why_this_matters": "Fact about a control for managing and mitigating the impact of physical security incidents."}, "Q_ASSET_INVENTORY_PHYSICAL": {"question_text": "Is there a current and accurate inventory of critical physical assets (e.g., servers, specialized equipment, sensitive documents) housed within this building?", "answer": "Yes", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "4. Emergency Preparedness and Operational Controls", "help_text": "Refers to an inventory of physical items, not just the building itself.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Fact about an administrative control that helps in asset tracking, recovery, and impact assessment during an incident.", "why_this_matters": "Fact about an administrative control that helps in asset tracking, recovery, and impact assessment during an incident."}, "Q_OVERALL_IMPACT_RATING": {"question_text": "Considering all identified risks and existing controls, what is the estimated overall ''Impact Rating'' if this Office Building were to be severely compromised (e.g., prolonged unavailability, major physical damage, significant security breach)?", "answer": "4 - High: Risk has serious impact on business and operations", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "5. Overall Risk Perspective", "help_text": "Rate the overall business impact using the organization''s scale (1-5). This is your overall business judgment, not a technical calculation.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Collects the asset owner''s high-level business perspective on potential harm, which is a critical input for Agent 2''s risk quantification.", "why_this_matters": "Collects the asset owner''s high-level business perspective on potential harm, which is a critical input for Agent 2''s risk quantification."}, "Q_OVERALL_PROBABILITY_RATING": {"question_text": "Considering all identified threats and vulnerabilities, what is the estimated ''Probability Rating'' of a severe compromise occurring to this Office Building within the next year?", "answer": "4 - High: Once every 1-3 months", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "5. Overall Risk Perspective", "help_text": "Rate the overall likelihood using the organization''s scale (1-5). This is your overall business judgment, not a technical calculation.\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Why this matters: Collects the asset owner''s high-level business perspective on the likelihood of an adverse event, which is a critical input for Agent 2''s risk quantification.", "why_this_matters": "Collects the asset owner''s high-level business perspective on the likelihood of an adverse event, which is a critical input for Agent 2''s risk quantification."}}, "questionnaire_metadata": {"source": "email", "token": "7c45c8d1-67eb-4512-bd83-af67c202cbc8", "completed_date": "2026-01-29 17:32:22", "total_answers": 24, "asset_type_assessed": "PHYSICAL ASSETS"}, "threats_and_vulnerabilities": [{"threat": "Unauthorized Physical Intrusion and Theft of Critical Assets", "threat_category": "Unauthorized physical access/ Physical theft", "contextual_description": "The Main Headquarters Building is vulnerable to unauthorized physical intrusion and theft, particularly outside business hours, due to reliance solely on ''Security Guards (Business Hours)'' for primary access control. The lack of active monitoring for installed CCTV cameras and only ''local alarms'' means that any unauthorized entry into critical areas like the IT data center or executive offices could go undetected for extended periods, allowing malicious actors (e.g., external criminals, disgruntled former employees) to steal sensitive equipment or intellectual property without immediate intervention or alert. This risk is amplified by the building housing critical functions and 1000 personnel, increasing potential targets and insider threat vectors.", "risk_statement": "Risk of unauthorized physical intrusion and theft of critical assets from the Main Headquarters Building due to limited physical access controls outside business hours, unmonitored CCTV, and local-only alarms, potentially causing loss of sensitive equipment, intellectual property, and business disruption.", "vulnerabilities": [{"vulnerability": "Lack of restrictions on physical entry and exit from the premises outside business hours.", "description": "Lack of restrictions on physical entry and exit from the premises outside business hours."}, {"vulnerability": "Inadequate physical monitoring of premises (CCTV not actively monitored).", "description": "Inadequate physical monitoring of premises (CCTV not actively monitored)."}, {"vulnerability": "Lack of central monitoring for alarm systems.", "description": "Lack of central monitoring for alarm systems."}], "evidence": ["3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts] Q: What primary physical access control systems are in place for the building perimeter and critical internal areas? \u2192 Answer: [''Security Guards (Business Hours)'']", "3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts] Q: Are surveillance cameras (CCTV) installed and actively monitored within and around the Office Building? \u2192 Answer: Yes, but not actively monitored", "3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts] Q: Are alarm systems (e.g., intrusion detection, motion sensors) installed and monitored? \u2192 Answer: Yes, local alarms only", "2. Business Context and Criticality] Q: Does this Office Building house any critical business functions or departments (e.g., data center, executive offices, primary call center)? \u2192 Answer: Yes", "2. Business Context and Criticality] Q: If ''Yes'' to the above, please list the critical business functions or departments housed within this building. \u2192 Answer: data center, executive offices, primary call center"], "threat_source": "Agent 0.5 (Email)"}, {"threat": "Data Center Outage and Building Damage due to Inadequate Fire Suppression", "threat_category": "Fire", "contextual_description": "The IT data center and other critical areas within the Main Headquarters Building are at high risk of significant damage and prolonged outage due to fire. The current fire suppression system relies solely on ''Fire Extinguishers,'' indicating a severe lack of automatic fire detection and suppression systems (e.g., sprinklers, gas suppression for data centers). A fire originating in the data center or other critical areas could rapidly spread, causing extensive damage to IT infrastructure, corporate administrative functions, and executive offices, leading to a complete cessation of IT service delivery, customer support, and product development, impacting 1000 personnel and critical business processes.", "risk_statement": "Risk of data center outage and extensive building damage from fire due to inadequate automatic fire detection and suppression systems, potentially causing prolonged business interruption, loss of critical IT services, and significant financial losses.", "vulnerabilities": [{"vulnerability": "Absence of adequate fire detection and firefighting equipment (e.g., sprinklers, automatic suppression systems).", "description": "Absence of adequate fire detection and firefighting equipment (e.g., sprinklers, automatic suppression systems)."}, {"vulnerability": "Lack of inspection / malfunctioning of fire-fighting, fire-suppression, fire alerting and fire exits (implied by only manual extinguishers).", "description": "Lack of inspection / malfunctioning of fire-fighting, fire-suppression, fire alerting and fire exits (implied by only manual extinguishers)."}, {"vulnerability": "Lack of monitoring procedures for temperature and humidity controls (for data center, increasing fire risk).", "description": "Lack of monitoring procedures for temperature and humidity controls (for data center, increasing fire risk)."}], "evidence": ["3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts] Q: What type of fire detection and suppression systems are installed in the building? \u2192 Answer: [''Fire Extinguishers'']", "2. Business Context and Criticality] Q: If ''Yes'' to the above, please list the critical business functions or departments housed within this building. \u2192 Answer: data center, executive offices, primary call center", "2. Business Context and Criticality] Q: Which key business processes are directly dependent on the continuous operation of this Office Building? \u2192 Answer: Daily administrative operations, IT service delivery, customer support, product development"], "threat_source": "Agent 0.5 (Email)"}, {"threat": "Prolonged Business Interruption from Environmental Disaster and Power Failure", "threat_category": "Flood, Earthquake, Storms/Wind/Lightning, Public Utilities Failure (Power/Water)", "contextual_description": "The Main Headquarters Building faces a high risk of prolonged business interruption from environmental disasters, including floods, seismic activity, and severe weather, given its location in a ''flood zone, seismic activity, severe weather'' prone area. This risk is compounded by the lack of redundant power sources for critical operations (only internet has redundancy), making the IT data center, executive offices, and primary call center highly susceptible to power outages during such events. A severe environmental incident could lead to physical damage, extended power loss, and unavailability of the building, severely impacting daily administrative operations, IT service delivery, customer support, and product development, affecting 1000 personnel.", "risk_statement": "Risk of prolonged business interruption to the Main Headquarters Building due to environmental disasters (flood, seismic activity, severe weather) and lack of redundant power for critical operations, potentially causing physical damage, extended unavailability of critical functions, and significant operational and financial losses.", "vulnerabilities": [{"vulnerability": "Lack of consideration towards siting of facility in areas susceptible to environmental risks (flood zone, seismic activity).", "description": "Lack of consideration towards siting of facility in areas susceptible to environmental risks (flood zone, seismic activity)."}, {"vulnerability": "Lack of adequate backup measures for backup power supply for critical operations.", "description": "Lack of adequate backup measures for backup power supply for critical operations."}, {"vulnerability": "L