d suppression systems, potentially causing prolonged business interruption, loss of critical IT services, and significant financial losses.", "vulnerabilities": [{"vulnerability": "Absence of adequate fire detection and firefighting equipment (e.g., sprinklers, automatic suppression systems).", "description": "Absence of adequate fire detection and firefighting equipment (e.g., sprinklers, automatic suppression systems)."}, {"vulnerability": "Lack of inspection / malfunctioning of fire-fighting, fire-suppression, fire alerting and fire exits (implied by only manual extinguishers).", "description": "Lack of inspection / malfunctioning of fire-fighting, fire-suppression, fire alerting and fire exits (implied by only manual extinguishers)."}, {"vulnerability": "Lack of monitoring procedures for temperature and humidity controls (for data center, increasing fire risk).", "description": "Lack of monitoring procedures for temperature and humidity controls (for data center, increasing fire risk)."}], "evidence": ["3. Physical Security and Environmental Facts] Q: What type of fire detection and suppression systems are installed in the building? \u2192 Answer: [''Fire Extinguishers'']", "2. Business Context and Criticality] Q: If ''Yes'' to the above, please list the critical business functions or departments housed within this building. \u2192 Answer: data center, executive offices, primary call center", "2. Business Context and Criticality] Q: Which key business processes are directly dependent on the continuous operation of this Office Building? \u2192 Answer: Daily administrative operations, IT service delivery, customer support, product development"], "threat_source": "Agent 0.5 (Email)"}, {"threat": "Prolonged Business Interruption from Environmental Disaster and Power Failure", "threat_category": "Flood, Earthquake, Storms/Wind/Lightning, Public Utilities Failure (Power/Water)", "contextual_description": "The Main Headquarters Building faces a high risk of prolonged b