: "High", "reasoning": "Q17 and Q18 confirm the building is in a ''flood zone, seismic activity, severe weather'' prone area, inherently increasing environmental threat probability. Q16 states redundant power is ''for internet only'', indicating a lack of backup power for critical operations. Q20 indicates the disaster recovery plan is ''documented but not tested'', increasing the likelihood of prolonged interruption."}, "risk_value": {"value": 16, "calculation": "4 (impact) \u00d7 4 (probability) = 16"}, "risk_evaluation_rating": {"rating": 4, "level": "NON-ACCEPTABLE", "mapping_rationale": "Risk value 16 maps to Risk Rating 4 (16 to 20) per discovered risk evaluation rating table."}, "risk_classification": {"classification": "NON-ACCEPTABLE", "criteria_applied": "Risks with a Risk Rating of 4 or 5 are Non-acceptable.", "justification": "Risk Rating 4 is non-acceptable per organizational policy."}}}',NULL);
