 "dropdown", "options": ["Closed"]}]}]}','{"risk_id": "RSK-029", "risk_description": "Exacerbated Impact from Incidents due to Untested Emergency and Incident Response Plans", "root_cause": "Threat: Exacerbated Impact from Incidents due to Untested Emergency and Incident Response Plans. Control Gaps: Emergency evacuation plan is not regularly practiced", "inherent_risk_rating": "4/5", "residual_risk": "3.67/5", "termination_justification": "The emergency and incident response plans have been deemed inadequate for the current threat landscape. The building''s emergency systems require complete overhaul which is not cost-effective. The organization has decided to relocate operations to a newer facility with modern safety systems.\n", "business_impact": "Minimal business impact as operations will be transferred to the new facility within 30 days. All critical functions have backup locations. Estimated cost savings of $50,000 annually by avoiding emergency system upgrades.\n", "approval_authority": "sakthivel , Chief Operating Officer (COO) and Facilities Director", "termination_actions": "1. Complete relocation of all operations to new facility by 2026/02/03\n2. Transfer all emergency response equipment to new location\n3. Conduct final safety audit and documentation\n4. Close building lease and terminate utility contracts\n5. Archive all incident response documentation\n", "completion_date": "2026-02-03", "closure_status": "Closed"}','sakthivel.r@yash.com','saved','2026-02-03 01:55:40','2026-02-03 02:01:32','{"agent_1": {"discovery_summary": {"cia_methodology": "CIA (Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability)", "cia_rating_scale": "4-level: Insignificant, Moderate, Serious, Extreme", "cia_definitions_source": "Asset Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx, Table 3", "business_value_calculation_method": "Asset Value Chart/Matrix", "business_value_levels": ["Very Low", "Low", "Medium", "High", "Very High"], "business_value_source": "Asset Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx, Table 3 and Risk Assessment Template_For Agentic AI RM Use Case.xlsx, Sheet: Asset Inventorization Guideline", "criticality_classification_method": "Business Value to Criticality Mapping", "criticality_levels": ["Insignificant", "Low Critical", "Medium Critical", "High Critical", "Very High Critical"], "criticality_source": "Asset Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx, Table 4 and Risk Assessment Template_For Agentic AI RM Use Case.xlsx, Sheet: Asset Inventorization Guideline", "searches_performed": ["What impact assessment methodology is used? CIA? DREAD? Custom?", "What rating scale is used for Confidentiality, Integrity, and Availability (CIA) impact ratings? What are the levels and definitions for each?", "How is Asset Business Value calculated or determined from CIA impact ratings? Is there a matrix, chart, or formula? What are the Asset Business Value levels?"]}, "threat_analysis": [{"threat_id": "threat_1", "threat_name": "Unauthorized Physical Intrusion and Theft of Critical Assets", "threat_description": "The Main Headquarters Building is vulnerable to unauthorized physical intrusion and theft, particularly outside business hours, due to reliance solely on ''Security Guards (Business Hours)'' for primary access control. The lack of active monitoring for installed CCTV cameras and only ''local alarms'' means that any unauthorized entry into critical areas like the IT data center or executive offices could go undetected for extended periods, allowing malicious actors (e.g., external criminals, disgruntled former employees) to steal sensitive equipment or intellectual property without immediate intervention or alert. This risk is amplified by the building housing critical functions and 1000 personnel, increasing potential targets and insider threat vectors.", "impact_assessment": {"confidentiality": {"rating": "Extreme", "numeric_value": 4, "reasoning": "Based on questionnaire facts stating ''steal sensitive equipment or intellectual property'' from ''IT data center, executive offices'', unauthorized disclosure would cause ''serious damage to the interests of the organization''. This meets the discovered definition for ''Extreme'': ''Unauthorized disclosure within or outside the organization would cause serious damage to the interests of the organization. Disclosure within the organization will be strictly on a \u2018need-to-know\u2019 basis.'' (Asset Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx, Table 3)."}, "integrity": {"rating": "Extreme", "numeric_value": 4, "reasoning": "Based on facts about ''steal sensitive equipment or intellectual property'', theft of critical assets could lead to their unauthorized modification or destruction, or the data on them. This would have a ''severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations''. This meets the discovered definition for ''Extreme'': ''Unauthorized modification or damage of information is expected to have severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations.'' (Asset Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx, Table 3)."}, "availability": {"rating": "Extreme", "numeric_value": 4, "reasoning": "Based on facts about ''steal sensitive equipment'' from ''IT data center, executive offices, primary call center'', this would lead to unavailability of assets and services. This would have a ''severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations''. This meets the discovered definition for ''Extreme'': ''Impact of disruption of access or unavailability of information or information asset or services is expected to have severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations.'' (Asset Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx, Table 3)."}}, "overall_impact_calculation": {"confidentiality_numeric": 4, "integrity_numeric": 4, "availability_numeric": 4, "calculation_method": "Maximum of C, I, A numeric values", "calculation": "max(4, 4, 4) = 4", "overall_impact": "High", "overall_impact_numeric": 4}}, {"threat_id": "threat_2", "threat_name": "Data Center Outage and Building Damage due to Inadequate Fire Suppression", "threat_description": "The IT data center and other critical areas within the Main Headquarters Building are at high risk of significant damage and prolonged outage due to fire. The current fire suppression system relies solely on ''Fire Extinguishers,'' indicating a severe lack of automatic fire detection and suppression systems (e.g., sprinklers, gas suppression for data centers). A fire originating in the data center or other critical areas could rapidly spread, causing extensive damage to IT infrastructure, corporate administrative functions, and executive offices, leading to a complete cessation of IT service delivery, customer support, and product development, impacting 1000 personnel and critical business processes.", "impact_assessment": {"confidentiality": {"rating": "Serious", "numeric_value": 3, "reasoning": "Based on questionnaire facts about ''extensive damage to IT infrastructure, corporate administrative functions, and executive offices'' due to fire, this could lead to destruction of sensitive data or exposure during recovery. This would cause ''significant harm to the interest of the organization''. This meets the discovered definition for ''Serious'': ''Unauthorized disclosure within or outside the organization would cause significant harm to the interest of the organization.'' (Asset Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx, Table 3)."}, "integrity": {"rating": "Extreme", "numeric_value": 4, "reasoning": "Based on facts about ''extensive damage to IT infrastructure'' and ''complete cessation of IT service delivery'', a fire would cause ''unauthorized modification or damage of information'' (destruction) with ''severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations''. This meets the discovered definition for ''Extreme'': ''Unauthorized modification or damage of information is expected to have severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations.'' (Asset Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx, Table 3)."}, "availability": {"rating": "Extreme", "numeric_value": 4, "reasoning": "Based on facts about ''prolonged outage'' and ''complete cessation of IT service delivery, customer support, and product development'' impacting ''1000 personnel and critical business processes'', this constitutes a ''severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations''. This meets the discovered definition for ''Extreme'': ''Impact of disruption of access or unavailability of information or information asset or services is expected to have severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations.'' (Asset Management Guidelines_For RM Agentic AI Use Case v1.0.docx, Table 3)."}}, "overall_impact_calculation": {"confidentiality_numeric": 3, "integrity_numeric": 4, "availability_numeric": 4, "calculation_method": "Maximum of C, I, A numeric values", "calculation": "max(3, 4, 4) = 4", "overall_impact": "High", "overall_impact_numeric": 4}}, {"threat_id": "threat_3", "threat_name": "Prolonged Business Interruption from Environmental Disaster and Power Failure", "threat_description": "The Main Headquarters Building faces a high risk of prolonged business interruption from environmental disasters, including floods, seismic activity, and severe weather, given its location in a ''flood zone, seismic activity, severe weather'' prone area. This risk is compounded by the lack of redundant power sources for critical operations (only internet has redundancy), making the IT data center, executive offices, and primary call center highly susceptible to power outages during such events. A severe environmental incident could lead to physical damage, extended power loss, and unavailability of the building, severely impacting daily administrative operations, IT service delivery, customer support, and product 