ion.''"}, "integrity": {"rating": "Extreme", "numeric_value": 5, "reasoning": "Based on the threat description ''widespread malware infection'' and ''disrupt the Manufacturing Line Control operations'', unauthorized modification or corruption of operational data and control systems is highly likely. This meets the discovered definition for ''Extreme'': ''Unauthorized modification or damage of information is expected to have severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations.''"}, "availability": {"rating": "Extreme", "numeric_value": 5, "reasoning": "Based on the threat description ''disrupt the Manufacturing Line Control operations'' and ''operational downtime'', the unavailability of critical manufacturing systems would have severe and long-ranging effects. This meets the discovered definition for ''Extreme'': ''Impact of disruption of access or unavailability of information or information asset or services is expected to have severe and long ranging adverse effect on business operations.''"}}, "overall_impact_calculation": {"confidentiality_numeric": 4, "integrity_numeric": 5, "availability_numeric": 5, "calculation_method": "max(C_numeric, I_numeric, A_numeric)", "calculation": "max(4, 5, 5) = 5", "overall_impact": "5 - Very High", "overall_impact_numeric": 5}}, {"threat_id": "threat_2", "threat_name": "Bypass of Endpoint Protection via Exploitation of Significant Exclusions", "threat_description": "The ''Company-wide Endpoint Protection Platform'' has ''significant exclusions'' configured in its policies, which protect 50 endpoints vital for ''Manufacturing Line Control''. While automatic updates and advanced features like DLP are in place, these exclusions represent a critical blind spot. A sophisticated attacker could leverage knowledge of these exclusions (e.g., specific files, folders, or processes necessary for manufacturing operations) to deploy malware or exfiltrate data undetected. This could lead to a compromise of the ''Manufacturing Line C