'Very High'', per the discovered Criticality Classification Table in organizational Asset Management Guidelines, the Asset Criticality Classification is ''Very high Critical''."}}, "agent_2_result": null, "agent_3_result": null, "agent_4_result": null, "agent_5_result": null, "last_updated": "2026-01-20 14:13:34", "progress": {"agent_1": "complete", "agent_2": "pending", "agent_3": "pending", "agent_4": "pending", "agent_5": "pending"}}','2026-02-03 19:29:41','2026-02-03 19:29:41');
INSERT INTO sessions VALUES(3,'session_Company-wide_Endpoint_Protecti_20260120_152450','{"session_id": "session_Company-wide_Endpoint_Protecti_20260120_152450", "asset_data": {"asset_name": "Company-wide Endpoint Protection Platform", "asset_type": "Software Assets", "asset_owner": "Abishek", "location": "On-premise Data Center - Rack 12", "description": "Manufacturing Line Control", "questionnaire_answers": {"Q_ASSET_CLASS_NAME": {"question_text": "What is the specific name/title of this Antivirus & Endpoint Security Software asset?", "answer": "Company-wide Endpoint Protection Platform", "question_type": "text", "section": "1. Asset Identification", "help_text": "e.g., ''Company-wide Endpoint Protection Platform'', ''Server Antivirus Solution'', ''Specific Vendor EDR System''", "why_this_matters": "Provides a unique identifier for the asset within the inventory."}, "Q_TYPE_OF_ASSET": {"question_text": "What type of asset is this?", "answer": "Software Assets", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "1. Asset Identification", "help_text": "Select the category that best describes this asset.", "why_this_matters": "Categorizes the asset according to organizational standards, aiding in consistent risk management."}, "Q_ASSET_CLASS_OWNER": {"question_text": "Who is the Asset Class Owner for this Antivirus & Endpoint Security Software?", "answer": "Abishek", "question_type": "text", "section": "1. Asset Identification", "help_text": "Provide the name or department responsible for the maintenance and implementation of controls on this asset.", "why_this_matters": "Identifies the primary stakeholder accountable for the asset''s security and operations."}, "Q_LOCATION": {"question_text": "Where is the primary management console or central server for this software located (physical or logical)?", "answer": "On-premise Data Center - Rack 12", "question_type": "text", "section": "1. Asset Identification", "help_text": "e.g., ''On-premise Data Center - Rack 12'', ''Cloud Provider - AWS Region us-east-1'', ''Managed by Vendor''", "why_this_matters": "Helps understand the physical/logical environment and potential environmental risks."}, "Q_BUSINESS_PROCESSES_DEPENDENT": {"question_text": "Which critical business processes or functions heavily depend on the protection provided by this Antivirus & Endpoint Security Software?", "answer": "Manufacturing Line Control", "question_type": "textarea", "section": "2. Business Context and Scope", "help_text": "List the key business operations that would be severely impacted if this software failed or was compromised. e.g., ''Customer Service Operations'', ''Financial Transactions Processing'', ''Manufacturing Line Control''", "why_this_matters": "Establishes the direct link between the asset''s security and core business operations, informing potential business impact."}, "Q_NUMBER_OF_ENDPOINTS_PROTECTED": {"question_text": "Approximately how many endpoints (e.g., workstations, servers, mobile devices) are protected by this software?", "answer": 50, "question_type": "number", "section": "2. Business Context and Scope", "help_text": "Provide an approximate count of devices under its protection.", "why_this_matters": "Indicates the scale of the asset''s deployment and the potential blast radius of a compromise."}, "Q_TYPES_OF_ENDPOINTS_PROTECTED": {"question_text": "What types of endpoints are protected by this software?", "answer": ["Windows Workstations", "Windows Servers", "Virtual Desktops (VDI)"], "question_type": "multiselect", "section": "2. Business Context and Scope", "help_text": "Select all applicable endpoint types. If ''Other'' is selected, please specify.", "why_this_matters": "Provides insight into the diversity and criticality of the protected environment, influencing potential vulnerabilities and impact."}, "Q_REAL_TIME_SCANNING_ENABLED": {"question_text": "Is real-time (on-access) scanning enabled on all protected endpoints?", "answer": "Partially", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "3. Software Configuration and Operational Facts", "help_text": "If partially, please describe which endpoints or conditions apply.", "why_this_matters": "Real-time scanning is a fundamental control for immediate threat detection. Its absence or partial implementation indicates a significant vulnerability."}, "Q_AUTOMATIC_UPDATES_ENABLED": {"question_text": "Are signature/definition updates and software version updates configured to occur automatically?", "answer": "Yes, both are automatic", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "3. Software Configuration and Operational Facts", "help_text": "Describe the frequency if manual, or any exceptions.", "why_this_matters": "Timely updates are crucial for protection against new threats. Manual processes introduce delays and potential for human error."}, "Q_CENTRALIZED_MANAGEMENT": {"question_text": "Is the Antivirus & Endpoint Security Software managed via a centralized console or platform?", "answer": "Yes", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "3. Software Configuration and Operational Facts", "help_text": "If managed by a third-party, please specify the provider.", "why_this_matters": "Centralized management allows for consistent policy enforcement, monitoring, and rapid response, reducing configuration drift and improving security posture."}, "Q_ADVANCED_FEATURES_ENABLED": {"question_text": "Which of the following advanced security features are enabled and actively used?", "answer": ["Device Control (e.g., USB blocking)", "Data Loss Prevention (DLP) capabilities"], "question_type": "multiselect", "section": "3. Software Configuration and Operational Facts", "help_text": "Select all features that are configured and operational.", "why_this_matters": "Indicates the depth of protection beyond basic antivirus, revealing the robustness of the endpoint security strategy."}, "Q_ADMIN_ACCESS_CONTROLS": {"question_text": "Are administrative access to the management console or individual endpoint agents protected by Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)?", "answer": "Yes, for all administrative access", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "3. Software Configuration and Operational Facts", "help_text": "Specify if there are exceptions.", "why_this_matters": "MFA is a critical control against unauthorized access to security management systems, preventing attackers from disabling protection."}, "Q_EXCLUSIONS_CONFIGURED": {"question_text": "Are there any significant exclusions (e.g., specific files, folders, processes) configured in the Antivirus & Endpoint Security Software policies?", "answer": "Yes, significant exclusions exist", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "3. Software Configuration and Operational Facts", "help_text": "If ''Yes, significant exclusions exist'', please briefly describe the nature of these exclusions and their justification.", "why_this_matters": "Exclusions can create blind spots for malware. Understanding their scope helps assess potential vulnerabilities."}, "Q_ALERTS_MONITORED": {"question_text": "Are alerts and logs generated by the Antivirus & Endpoint Security Software actively monitored?", "answer": "Yes, 24/7 by security operations center (SOC)", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "4. Monitoring and Incident Response", "help_text": "Specify who performs the monitoring if applicable.", "why_this_matters": "Active monitoring ensures that detected threats are promptly addressed, reducing the window of exposure."}, "Q_INTEGRATION_SIEM": {"question_text": "Are logs and alerts from this software integrated with a Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) system or other central logging solution?", "answer": "Yes", "question_type": "dropdown", "section": "4. Monitoring and Incident Response", "help_text": "If yes, specify the SIEM/logging solution.", "why_this_matters": "Integration with a SIEM enhances threat correlation, centralized visibility, and overall incident detection capabilities."}, "Q_INCIDENT_RESPONSE_PLAN": {"question_text":