al Control Facts] Q: Are there organizational policies or guidelines in place regarding the physical security of employee laptops (e.g., ''do not leave unattended'', ''secure in office'')?  Answer: Yes, but not strictly enforced", "5. Physical & Environmental Control Facts] Q: How frequently does this Employee Laptop travel outside of secure corporate premises (e.g., for business travel, remote work from public places)?  Answer: Occasionally (1-3 times a month)", "4. Technical & Security Configuration Facts] Q: Does the organization have the capability to remotely wipe or lock this Employee Laptop if it is lost or stolen?  Answer: Unknown", "3. Data Stored & Processed] Q: What is the highest data classification level of information typically stored or processed on this Employee Laptop?  Answer: Restricted", "3. Data Stored & Processed] Q: Does this Employee Laptop store or process any of the following sensitive data types?  Answer: [''PHI'', ''PII'', ''PCI_DSS'', ''Financial_Proprietary'']", "3. Data Stored & Processed] Q: Estimate the volume of sensitive data (if any) stored on this laptop.  Answer: Medium (e.g., hundreds of documents/records)", "4. Technical & Security Configuration Facts] Q: Is full disk encryption enabled and enforced on this Employee Laptop (e.g., BitLocker, FileVault)?  Answer: Yes"], "risk_statement": "Risk of physical theft of John Doe''s Laptop and subsequent data exposure due to non-enforcement of physical security policies and unknown remote wipe/lock capabilities, potentially causing unauthorized disclosure of Restricted data (PHI, PII, PCI_DSS, Financial_Proprietary), regulatory non-compliance, and reputational damage.", "threat_source": "Threat Vocabulary Database | RAG Discovery | Intelligent Analysis"}, {"threat_id": "T4", "threat_category": "Unintentional failure of IT systems (hardware/software)", "threat_name": "Data Loss or Corruption from System Failure or Undetected Malware", "contextual_description": "John Doe''s Laptop, criti